Two pointers

3. Longest Substring Without Repeating Characters:
   keep a hashmap which stores the characters in string as keys and their positions as values, and keep two pointers which
   define the max substring. move the right pointer to scan through the string , and meanwhile update the hashmap. If the
   character is already in the hashmap, then move the left pointer to the right of the same character last found.
   
